                            <comment id="13016276" author="jeffrey_chang" created="Wed, 6 Apr 2011 06:41:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Modified both index.jsp and form.jsp to return false upon JS submit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13016281" author="thetaphi" created="Wed, 6 Apr 2011 07:15:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Jeffrey,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thaks for the fix. This is really an issue and has nothing to do with Internet Explorer. The timing of the javascript calls in this browser just make it happen. In general: onclick handlers in javascript &lt;b&gt;must&lt;/b&gt; return false to prevent the default action. This is true in all browsers. You can try this out with a simple web page link: &amp;lt;a href=&quot;gohere&quot; onclick=&quot;window.alert(&apos;clicked&apos;); return true;&quot;&amp;gt;..&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;. This link will first display the message box and then go to &quot;gohere&quot; (in all browsers!), versus &amp;lt;a href=&quot;gohere&quot; onclick=&quot;window.alert(&apos;clicked&apos;); return false;&quot;&amp;gt;..&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt; will only display the message box.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another fix for this would be to simply remove form.submit() and explicitely return true.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13016291" author="thetaphi" created="Wed, 6 Apr 2011 07:50:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed trunk revision 1089335, branch 3.x revision 1089340&lt;/p&gt;

